body:
My custom router methods like the one below stopped working! I think this is pretty useful to be private :)

```swift
    @discardableResult public func options<T>(_ path: PathComponentsRepresentable..., use closure: @escaping (Request) throws -> T) -> Route<Responder> where T: ResponseEncodable {
        return self.on(.OPTIONS, at: path, use: closure)
    }
```

Done so statuses can be returned on their own.

Example:
```
        versionOneGroup.delete('park') { (req)  in
            return req.withConnection(to: .sqlite) { (db) in
                return db.query(Parking.self).first().flatMap(to: HTTPStatus.self) {
                    guard let park = '0 else {
                        throw Abort(.notFound, reason: 'Could not find parking.')
                    }

                    return park.delete(on: db).transform(to: HTTPStatus.ok)
                }
            }
        }
```
